reviews.review_text:
My time coming any old day... Love the set list for this show,
Lazy Lightning>Supplication
Sugaree
Not even sure i could fantasy set that in a million years.
Samson
B.E.Woman
plus Keith has some good piano in Samson
groovy show!
May 77 is kinda like Dead 73 --More or less perfect
All Scarlet Begonias are a touch of the blues...
Pure gold Extraordinary show, as most MN shows tend to be, but the sound quality of this board is something special. I have the official box release, but I think this might sound better.
Always loved... This Supplication. For some reason, over the years, it has always reminded as one of my (many) favorite GD interludes.

Anouther great show from 77 Enjoyed the show from beginning to end. Great quality on the audio hard to ask for more. Looks like rain really stood out as one of the best versions I've heard yet. Brown eyed women was also fantastic and definitely a highlight. If you haven't yet give this show a listen great audio and the boys where playing great, enjoy it.
